This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and speech recognition, which are both subfields of computer science. The paper specifically focuses on using a model for direct speech-to-text translation, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques for classification, which could fall under several sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of working with limited resources, which could fall under the category of software development (cs.SD).
